-- Italian Government Should Change to Rules That Hurt Banks, Guzzetti Says
-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i   a n d   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2010-10-28T08:49:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/italian-government-should-change-to-rules-that-hurt-banks-guzzetti-says.html
The Italian government should
consider changing rules that hurt bank competitiveness amid new
global rules on capital requirements, Giuseppe Guzzetti,
chairman of Acri, the bank foundation industry group.  Italian banks are penalized by the treatment of tax assets,
he said, speaking at a conference in Rome today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net  